that from space.

00:09:58.243 --> 00:09:59.660 align:middle line:84%
There are many
directions we could

00:09:59.660 --> 00:10:01.265 align:middle line:90%
go to continue this search.

00:10:01.265 --> 00:10:03.140 align:middle line:84%
It's just that James
Webb's got a good chance

00:10:03.140 --> 00:10:04.015 align:middle line:90%
of finding something.

00:10:04.015 --> 00:10:06.320 align:middle line:84%
And the amount of mysteries,
just natural mysteries,

00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:08.450 align:middle line:84%
that'll come from this
telescope is staggering.

00:10:08.450 --> 00:10:15.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, I don't think that
most people understand

00:10:15.140 --> 00:10:18.800 align:middle line:84%
the importance of what is
actually going on here.

00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:21.740 align:middle line:84%
