find an exoplanet.

00:10:21.740 --> 00:10:24.770 align:middle line:84%
But it's another thing
to be able to peer

00:10:24.770 --> 00:10:30.650 align:middle line:84%
into that exoplanet atmosphere
that is uncountable light

00:10:30.650 --> 00:10:31.520 align:middle line:90%
years away.

00:10:31.520 --> 00:10:35.960 align:middle line:84%
We obviously cannot see it, but
we can through the James Webb,

00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:40.710 align:middle line:84%
and look at its atmosphere and
see what is happening on that

00:10:40.710 --> 00:10:41.510 align:middle line:90%
planet.

00:10:41.510 --> 00:10:44.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, even if you don't
see a biosignature or anything

00:10:44.360 --> 00:10:47.750 align:middle line:84%
