00:10:52.770 --> 00:10:56.270 align:middle line:84%
But what else is possible that
we don't have an example of?

00:10:56.270 --> 00:10:59.468 align:middle line:84%
What interesting
scientific profiling,

00:10:59.468 --> 00:11:01.010 align:middle line:84%
which is important
to people like me,

00:11:01.010 --> 00:11:02.630 align:middle line:84%
science fiction
authors, where you

00:11:02.630 --> 00:11:04.580 align:middle line:84%
want to try to imagine
what alien planets look

00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:05.810 align:middle line:90%
like up close.

00:11:05.810 --> 00:11:10.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, what does a different
atmospheric makeup mean?

00:11:10.050 --> 00:11:12.290 align:middle line:84%
Do you even need the
atmosphere that we

00:11:12.290 --> 00:11:14.180 align:middle line:90%
have for a situation for life?

00:11:14.180 --> 00:11:17.520 align:middle line:84%
Or could some weird other
mix of gases happen?

00:11:17.520 --> 00:11:18.890 align:middle line:90%
So those questions are all open.

00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:26.300 align:middle line:84%
