and took another look

00:16:59.660 --> 00:17:02.030 align:middle line:84%
at this star thinking, well,
that was a pretty weird star.

00:17:02.030 --> 00:17:02.780 align:middle line:90%
We should take a look.

00:17:02.780 --> 00:17:05.119 align:middle line:84%
They looked at it, and they
found transuranic elements

00:17:05.119 --> 00:17:09.230 align:middle line:84%
in it-- plutonium and higher
in the periodic table that

00:17:09.230 --> 00:17:12.980 align:middle line:84%
shouldn't exist in those
numbers in nature, suggestive

00:17:12.980 --> 00:17:15.500 align:middle line:84%
of physics, of some type
of island of stability,

00:17:15.500 --> 00:17:19.520 align:middle line:84%
where there's a stability way
up there that things decay down

00:17:19.520 --> 00:17:20.525 align:middle line:90%
and come down to.

00:17:20.525 --> 00:17:22.400 align:middle line:84%
The thing is, you need
something making that.

00:17:22.400 --> 00:17:25.970 align:middle line:84%
You need a neutron star
bombarding this otherwise

00:17:25.970 --> 00:17:29.300 align:middle line:84%
normal star to get some kind
of nuclear weirdness going,

00:17:29.300 --> 00:17:30.420 align:middle line:90%
and that isn't occurring.

00:17:30.420 --> 00:17:32.450 align:middle line:84%
So why this thing--
this is the only star

00:17:32.450 --> 00:17:35.420 align:middle line:84%
we've ever seen that has
these elements in it.

00:17:35.420 --> 00:17:38.600 align:middle line:84%
If they are indeed there and
it's not a measurement problem,

00:17:38.600 --> 00:17:40.910 align:middle line:84%
well, that could be a
technosignature very easily.

00:17:40.910 --> 00:17:43.820 align:middle line:84%
And it was actually advanced as
a technosignature-- plutonium

00:17:43.820 --> 00:17:45.860 align:middle line:84%
and a star, salting a
star with plutonium,

00:17:45.860 --> 00:17:48.770 align:middle line:84%
by Carl Sagan and
Joseph Shklovsky

00:17:48.770 --> 00:17:51.470 align:middle line:84%
way back in the 1960s,
that if you ever

00:17:51.470 --> 00:17:53.690 align:middle line:84%
saw that, it's a
good technosignature.

00:17:53.690 --> 00:17:57.470 align:middle line:84%
>> You've been writing
about this for so long now.

